<br/>
<li>No major design changes are expected</li></ul>
<br/>

<br/>
<h2>14-Inch and 16-Inch MacBook Pro With M4 Pro and M4 Max Chips</h2>
<br/>
<ul><li>The already-announced M4 Pro chip has <a href=\"https://www.macrumors.com/2024/10/29/apple-announces-m4-pro-chip/\">up to a 14-core CPU and up to a 20-core GPU</a></li>
<br/>
<li><a href=\"https://www.macrumors.com/2024/10/29/new-mac-mini-hints-at-macbook-pro-ram/\">A minimum of 24GB of RAM is expected</a> for 14-inch and 16-inch MacBook Pro models with the M4 Pro chip</li>
<br/>
<li><a href=\"https://www.macrumors.com/2024/10/29/m4-macbook-pro-likely-feature-thunderbolt-5/\">Thunderbolt 5 support is likely</a> for up to 120 Gb/s data transfer speeds</li>
<br/>
<li>No major design changes are expected</li></ul>
